---
hero:
  title: '_Clear_ metrics. _Reliable_ data. Decisions you can _trust_.'
  subtitle: 'dyvenia helps enterprises align and validate their metrics so leaders can trust their numbers, scale analytics, and deploy AI with confidence.'
  button_text: Schedule a discovery call
  button_target: https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/alessio-civitillo/book-a-call
  video: ./src/assets/videos/jellyfish-1.mp4
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/jellyfish-hr.jpg
intro:
  title:
    Most companies don’t actually struggle with data.
    **They struggle with the context behind it.**
  content_left: |-
    Data exists across multiple systems, teams, and processes, but it is rarely structured in a way that preserves its business meaning, breaking trust.
  content_right: |-
    - Data lives across ERPs, CRMs, and operational systems
    - Metrics defined differently across functions
    - Business context gets lost when data is combined across sources
highlight_one:
  title: We build data foundations that preserve business context and make metrics consistent across the organization
  subtitle: by working backwards from the decisions leaders need to make, we design data models, pipelines, and platforms that ensure metrics are aligned, traceable, and scalable across systems.
highlight_two:
  title1: The Goal?
  title2: From fragmented data to consistent, decision-ready metrics
  content: We help organizations move from disconnected systems and conflicting reports to a shared, reliable foundation for decision-making.
foundations_titles:
  title1: Business outcomes you can
  title2: TRUST
foundations_elements:
  - title: Aligned metrics across teams
    content: Finance, operations, and sales rely on the same definitions, eliminating debates and reconciliation.
  - title: Trustworthy, traceable data
    content: Every number can be explained back to its source, making analytics auditable and reliable.
  - title: AI-ready foundations
    content: Curated facts and dimensions ensure AI pilots produce consistent, explainable outputs.
  - title: Faster, smarter decisions
    content: Teams spend less time validating data and more time acting on insights.
  - title: Scalable analytics
    content: Data models and pipelines grow with your organization without breaking consistency or performance.
about:
  title: Who We Are
  content: |-
    We are data and performance management specialists with backgrounds in finance, operations, and analytics.

    We have worked in the same environments our clients operate in, where metrics don’t align, data comes from multiple systems, and reporting requires constant validation.

    We focus on building **data foundations that reflect real business processes**, so the numbers leaders rely on are consistent, explainable, and actionable.

    We believe **AI is a competitive advantage only if it’s built on reliable data and a clear business context**. That’s what we deliver.
whyus_intro:
  title: What’s Holding You Back
  content: Enterprises are drowning in data, but struggling to turn it into performance.
whyus_elements:
  - title: Slow Insights
    content: By the time reports are ready, the opportunity has passed.
  - title: Disconnected numbers
    content: Finance, sales, and operations spend time reconciling conflicting results.
  - title: Unreliable AI outputs
    content: Without clear metrics and structure, AI produces inconsistent answers.
  - title: Fragmented systems
    content: ERP, CRM, and operational data remain difficult to combine meaningfully.
  - title: Growing pressure on teams
    content: FP&A and operations are expected to deliver faster, with greater accuracy.
  - title: Unclear ownership of metrics
    content: No single source of truth makes accountability and trust difficult.
our_services:
  title: How We Deliver Results
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-dyvenia26.jpg
our_services_items:
  - title: Services
    prefix: Consulting
    description: |-
      We fix the foundations so your data and AI deliver measurable impact:

      - **Data Engineering** – Ingest, clean, and unify ERP, CRM, and operational data.
      - **Analytics & BI** – Build business-relevant models, dashboards, and KPI frameworks.
      - **Performance Management** – Enable rolling forecasts, what-if scenarios, and dynamic planning.
      - **AI Readiness** – Governance and data standards to make AI outputs trustworthy.
  - title: AI Assistant
    prefix: Perspeqtive
    description: |-
      Your team’s fastest route to insights. Ask questions in plain language and get instant answers:

      - **On-demand charts**, metrics, and explanations.
      - Ready-to-run **SQL queries**, no coding required.
      - **Always connected** to ERP, CRM, and finance systems.
      - Shared definitions across teams for **consistent KPIs**.
description: Driving Better Decisions and Business Performance with Unified Metrics
bodyClass: home
mainClass: "scroll-fade-up-h2s"
blog:
  title: Our Insights
  intro: Selected Articles. Check our blog for more.
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: dyvenia
---

{% set customHero = {
  hero: hero,
  height: "cover",
  content_inline: "left",
  region_space: "xl-2xl",
  button_variant: "blue"
} %}
{% include "partials/custom-hero.njk" %}


<div class="intro | wrapper">
  <article class="prose region flow feature">
    <h2>{{ intro.title | markdownInline | safe }}</h2>
      <div class="grid" data-layout="50-50">
          <div class="text-step-1">{{ intro.content_left | markdownFormat | safe }}</div>
          <div>{{ intro.content_right | markdownFormat | safe }}</div>
      </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="highlight-one | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent)">
    <article class="full  intro | section__inner wrapper  region">
      <div class="feature flow prose">
        <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ highlight_one.title }} <span>*</span></h2>
        <p class="text-step-min-1"><span>*</span> {{ highlight_one.subtitle }}</p>
      </div>
      {% svg "brand/waves" %}
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="highlight-two | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent-6)">
    <article class="full intro | section__inner wrapper region flow prose text-center text-blue-100">
      <h2 class="text-step-1 feature">
        {{ highlight_two.title1 }}
        <span class="block text-step-4 text-blue-400 mt-2xs">{{ highlight_two.title2 }} </span>
      </h2>
      <p class="flow-space-l">{{ highlight_two.content }}</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="foundations | wrapper">
  <article class="full region flow">
    <h2 class="text-step-3 text-center">
      {{ foundations_titles.title1 }}
      <span class="block uppercase text-blue-500">{{ foundations_titles.title2 }} </span>
    </h2>
    <div class="split region">
      {% svg "brand/medusa-organic" %}
      <ol class="timeline">
        {% for key in foundations_elements %}
          <li>
            <span>{{ loop.index }}</span>
            <div class="flow flow-space-3xs">
              <h3 class="text-step-1">{{ key.title }}</h3>
              <p>{{ key.content }}</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="about | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region">
    <header class="grid intro" data-layout="thirds">
      <h2>{{ about.title }}</h2>
      <div class="flow">{{ about.content | markdownFormat | safe }}</div>
    </header>
    {% set orderedTeamMembers = collections.team_members | sortByOrderIndex %}
    <div class="grid team mt-xl-2xl" data-layout="thirds">
      {% for member in orderedTeamMembers %}
      {% if member.data.show_on_about %}
        <custom-card clickable small-padding img-3-2>
          {% image "." + member.data.image, "" %}
          <h3 class="text-step-1" slot="headline"><a href="{{ member.url }}">{{ member.data.name }}</a>  {% if member.data.role %}
              <span class="text-step-min-1 font-bold">{{ member.data.role }}</span>
            {% endif %}</h3>
          <div slot="content" webc:nokeep>
            {{ member.data.description_short | markdownFormat | safe }}
          </div>
        </custom-card>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="why | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region flow">
    <header class="flow">
    <h2 class="heading-line">{{ whyus_intro.title }}</h2>
      {{ whyus_intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
      </header>

      <dl class="flow region column" role="list">
        {% for key in whyus_elements %}
          <div class="flow">
            <dt class="font-bold text-purple">{{ key.title }}</dt>
            <dd>{{ key.content }}</dd>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </dl>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="services | wrapper">

  {% if our_services.image %}
  {% image our_services.image, "" %}
  {% endif %}

    <article class="wrapper region flow">
        <h2 class="text-center">{{ our_services.title }}</h2>

          {% for item in our_services_items %}

            <div class="grid" data-layout="thirds">
              <h3>{{ item.prefix }} <span>{{ item.title }}</span></h3>
              <div>
              {{ item.description | markdownFormat | safe }}
            </div>
            </div>

          {% endfor %}
    </article>

</div>

<div class="blog | wrapper">
  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2><a class="no-underline hover:underline" href="/insights/">{{ blog.title }}</a></h2>

      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="feature">
        <div class="grid gutter-s" data-layout='thirds'>

         {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
         {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 3) %}
         {% set showTags = false %}
         {% set headingLevel = "h3" %}
           {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
         {% endeach %}

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

{%- css "local" -%}
  {%- include "css/custom-hero.css" -%}
  {%- include 'css/home.css' -%}
  {%- include 'css/column.css' -%}
  {%- include "css/custom-card.css" -%}
{%- endcss -%}
